(61, 1, '2011-02-28 19:23:27', '2011-02-28 19:23:27', '<p>\r\n	From <a href=\"http://directorblue.blogspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Doug Ross</a>:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>This looks at the inspiration for the Constitution (history, philosophy), as well as how we&#39;ve gone astray. </em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJxCXDoTuI/AAAAAAAAWnI/M9ucL8c2hnc/s1600-h/091011-o-temple.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"1\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5391495989278822114\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJxCXDoTuI/AAAAAAAAWnI/M9ucL8c2hnc/s400/091011-o-temple.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 200px;\" /></a><i><span style=\"font-family: georgia; font-size: 9pt;\">&ldquo;Greece would not have fallen had it obeyed Polybius in everything, and when Greece did meet disaster, its only help came from him&rdquo; Pausanias, 8.37.2, Inscription on the Temple of Despoina near Arakesion.</span></i><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJviv3fVvI/AAAAAAAAWmA/mRwhbDGnbzk/s1600-h/091011-con-polybius.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"1\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5391494346671347442\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJviv3fVvI/AAAAAAAAWmA/mRwhbDGnbzk/s400/091011-con-polybius.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 199px;\" /></a>In Book VI of his <u>Histories</u>, the ancient Greek historian Polybius described three basic forms of government, each categorized by the number of those in power. He listed monarchy (rule by the one); aristocracy (rule by the few); and democracy (rule by the many). Polybius described, over time, how each type of government would gradually decline into their various corrupted forms of tyranny, oligarchy and mob rule, respectively.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJvsk497sI/AAAAAAAAWmw/3fq4XRMkiqY/s1600-h/091011-con-fall-of-rome2.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"1\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5391494515523448514\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJvsk497sI/AAAAAAAAWmw/3fq4XRMkiqY/s400/091011-con-fall-of-rome2.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 200px;\" /></a>Polybius believed that Republican Rome had designed a new form of government that could help check this inevitable decline. Rome combined all three forms of government -- monarchy (its elected executives, called consuls); aristocracy (the Senate); and democracy (the popular assemblies). In this mixed form of goverment, each branch would check the corrupting ambitions and power of the others.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://directorblue.blogspot.com/2011/02/fork-in-road.html\" target=\"_blank\">Read more ...</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>\r\n	From <a href=\"http://ace.mu.nu/\" target=\"_blank\">Ace of Spades HQ</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>Regardless of your feelings about last year&#39;s health care legislation or whether he is right, what&#39;s important here is that he is looking at the consitition, the law, judicial history, and common sense to form an opinion. </em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Someone was questioning my thoughts that the ObamaCare suit was an underdog. Here&#39;s some reasons it just might work.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The claim of constitutionality for ObamaCare rests upon two clauses of the Constitution (plus lots of interpretation and expansion since they were written).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Commerce Clause authorizes Congress to regulate commerce between the states. This has been interpreted, rather expansively, as giving commerce the authority to regulate anything that &quot;affects&quot; interstate commerce, even if the action is itself entirely intrastate.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Example: Federal law controls how much corn you can grow. People challenged this, saying &quot;Okay, I&#39;m growing more corn than you allow, but it&#39;s not being sold to citizens of other states, but only within my state to other citizens within my state where the federal law can&#39;t touch me.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Held: If you sell the corn to intrastate customers, that means their need for corn from out of the state is therefore diminished, so your sale prevents (or discourages) an interstate sale, so it &quot;affects&quot; interstate commerce.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://ace.mu.nu/archives/312142.php\" target=\"_blank\">Read more ...</a></p>\r\n', 'A couple recent constitution-related articles I liked', '<p>\r\n	From <a href=\"http://directorblue.blogspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Doug Ross</a>:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>This looks at the inspiration for the Constitution (history, philosophy), as well as how we&#39;ve gone astray. </em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJxCXDoTuI/AAAAAAAAWnI/M9ucL8c2hnc/s1600-h/091011-o-temple.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"1\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5391495989278822114\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJxCXDoTuI/AAAAAAAAWnI/M9ucL8c2hnc/s400/091011-o-temple.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 200px;\" /></a><i><span style=\"font-family: georgia; font-size: 9pt;\">&ldquo;Greece would not have fallen had it obeyed Polybius in everything, and when Greece did meet disaster, its only help came from him&rdquo; Pausanias, 8.37.2, Inscription on the Temple of Despoina near Arakesion.</span></i><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJviv3fVvI/AAAAAAAAWmA/mRwhbDGnbzk/s1600-h/091011-con-polybius.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"1\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5391494346671347442\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_orkXxp0bhEA/StJviv3fVvI/AAAAAAAAWmA/mRwhbDGnbzk/s400/091011-con-polybius.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 199px;\" /></a>In Book VI of his <u>Histories</u>, the ancient Greek histo