(725, 1, '2013-08-31 01:04:34', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'So the book the Liberty Amendments is available and thought provoking, imho. There are 10 proposed amendments, whose merits can be debated, but his primary premise is bypassing Washington in a considered, thoughtful way.\r\n\r\nIt\'s basically that article V allows two methods of amending the constitution: The one that\'s been used and the one that bypasses congress. Constitutional scholars may disagree on the purview of Article 5, but it does open up a discussion of where we are as far as liberty. His first amendment is term limits for congress. His limit of 12 year combined service could be debated, but come on, U.S. Term Limits, Inc. v. Thornton assured that states could not enforce their own term limits on their own representatives, our blessed representatives are not going to term limit themselves,', 'Liberty Amenments', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-08-31 01:04:34', '2013-08-31 01:04:34', '', 0, 'http://ttmsoia.andyhill.us/?p=725', 0, 'post', '', 0),
