(929, 1, '2014-04-29 21:23:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<strong>Discriminate</strong> (according to <a href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/discriminate\" target=\"_blank\">dictionary.com</a>):\n\n<strong>Etymology</strong>\n<blockquote>\n<div>1620s, from L. discriminare \"to divide,\" from discrimen, derived n. from discernere (see <a id=\"dic_result\" href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/discern\">discern</a>). The adverse (usually racial) sense is first recorded 1866, Amer.Eng. Positive sense remains in <a id=\"dic_result\" href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/discriminating\">discriminating</a>. Related: Discriminated</div>\n<div></div></blockquote>\n<div><strong>From the Definition</strong></div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>\n<div><strong>verb (used without object), dis·crim·i·nat·ed, dis·crim·i·nat·ing.</strong>\n<div>1. to make a distinction in favor of or against a person or thing on the basis of the group, class, or category to <a href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/which\">which</a> the person or thing belongs rather than according to actual merit; show partiality: The new law discriminates against foreigners. He discriminates in favor of his relatives.</div>\n<div>2. to note or observe a difference; distinguish accurately: to discriminate between things.</div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n</div></blockquote>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div><strong>Analysis</strong></div>\n<div>Note that the second definition is more in line with the etymology (dividing), but the first definition is in more popular use. I discriminate by merely <em>noticing</em> that you are blonde versus brunette, left-handed versus right-handed, pants sagging or not, etc.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>I think \'discriminate (1)\'  is intellectually lazy. \"Discriminates against\" is Orwellian when looking at the term\'s origin.  Actually, it\'s not Orwellian, it\'s a non sequitor.</div>', 'Don\'t Discriminate', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'dont-discriminate', '', '', '2014-04-29 21:23:30', '2014-04-30 02:23:30', '', 0, 'http://ttmsoia.andyhill.us/?p=929', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(930, 1, '2014-04-29 21:22:27', '2014-04-30 02:22:27', '<strong>Discriminate</strong> (according to <a href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/discriminate\" target=\"_blank\">dictionary.com</a>):\r\n\r\n<strong>Etymology</strong>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>1620s, from L. discriminare \"to divide,\" from discrimen, derived n. from discernere (see <a id=\"dic_result\" href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/discern\">discern</a>). The adverse (usually racial) sense is first recorded 1866, Amer.Eng. Positive sense remains in <a id=\"dic_result\" href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/discriminating\">discriminating</a>. Related: Discriminated</div>\r\n<div></div></blockquote>\r\n<div><strong>From the Definition</strong></div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>verb (used without object), dis·crim·i·nat·ed, dis·crim·i·nat·ing.</strong>\r\n<div>1. to make a distinction in favor of or against a person or thing on the basis of the group, class, or category to <a href=\"http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/which\">which</a> the person or thing belongs rather than according to actual merit; show partiality: The new law discriminates against foreigners. He discriminates in favor of his relatives.</div>\r\n<div>2. to note or observe a difference; distinguish accurately: to discriminate between things.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div></blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Analysis</strong></div>\r\n<div>Note that the second definition is more in line with the etymology (dividing), but the first definition is in more popular use. I discriminate by merely <em>noticing</em> that you are blonde versus brunette, left-handed versus right-handed, pants sagging or not, etc.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>I think \'discriminate (1)\'  is intellectually lazy. \"Discriminates against\" is Orwellian when looking at the term\'s origin.  Actually, it\'s not Orwellian, it\'s a non sequitor.</div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div></blockquote>', 'Don\'t Discriminate', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '929-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-29 21:22:27', '2014-04-30 02:22:27', '', 929, 'http://ttmsoia.andyhill.us/2014/04/29/929-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
